        <h1>Cloud Computing Question Bank 2079 - 2079</h1>
        <p><strong>Full Marks:</strong> 160 + 40</p>
        <p><strong>Pass Marks:</strong> 64 + 16</p>
        <p><strong>Time:</strong> 3 hours</p>
    <h2>SECTION A: Attempt any TWO question.</h2><h3>Question 1</h3>
<div><p><p>Define cloud computing. Discuss various cloud deployment models.</p>
<p> </p</p></div><div><strong>Answer:</strong><br><style>body .mathjax_wrap{width: 100%;overflow-x: scroll;margin-bottom:10px;}</style><p>Cloud computing is the on demand delivery of computing services such as servers, networking software etc ovet the internet. Rather thn keeping the files on a physical storage device, cloud computing makes it possible to save remotely. Various cloud deployment models are discussed below:</p>
<p><strong>Public cloud</strong></p>
<ul style="list-style-type: square;">
<li>They are owned and operated bu 3rd party cloud service providers, such as AWS, Microsoft Azure and Google cloud.</li>
<li>These cloud services are accessible to general public over the internet, allowing multiple organization or individual to share computing resources, such as server, storage and networks.</li>
<li>They offer scalability, flexibility, and cost effectivness as user can pay for resources on a pay-as-you-go basis.</li>
</ul>
<p><em>Advantages</em>:</p>
<ol style="list-style-type:decimal;">
<li>Cost effective : Resources are shared with large number of user.</li>
<li>Flexibility : Easy to integrate public cloud with private.</li>
<li>Location independence : Services are delivered through internet.</li>
<li>High scalability</li>
</ol>
<p><em>Disadvantage</em>:</p>
<ol style="list-style-type:decimal;">
<li>Low security and less customizable.</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>Private cloud</strong></p>
<ul style="list-style-type: square;">
<li>They are dedicated cloud environments exclusively used by a single orginization. They can be hosted either on physical location within an org&#8217;s data centeror by a third party provider.</li>
<li>It offers greater control, security and customization compared to public cloud.</li>
</ul>
<p><em>Advantage</em>:</p>
<ol style="list-style-type:decimal;">
<li>Higher security and privacy, more control, cost efficiency</li>
</ol>
<p><em>Disadvantage</em>:</p>
<ol style="list-style-type:decimal;">
<li>Restricted, limited scalability.</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>Hybrid cloud</strong></p>
<ul style="list-style-type: square;">
<li>It combines public and private cloud environment allowing orgs to get the benefits of both. They can run certain workloads or application on-premises in private cloud while utilizing public cloud service for others.</li>
</ul>
<p><em>Advantage</em>:</p>
<ol style="list-style-type:decimal;">
<li>Scalability offers features of both, more security for private cloud.</li>
</ol>
<p><em>Disadvantage</em>:</p>
<ol style="list-style-type:decimal;">
<li>Networking issue due to presence of both clouds.</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>Community cloud</strong></p>
<ul style="list-style-type: square;">
<li>They are shared cloud environments that are tailored to the specific needs of a particular community or group of orgs with shared intrest or requirements.</li>
<li>They are managed and operated by 3rd party provides and offer collaberative capabilities, cost-sharing benefits and specialized features or services to meet the needs of the community members.</li>
</ul>
<p><em>Advantage</em>:</p>
<ol style="list-style-type:decimal;">
<li>Cost effective and security.</li>
</ol>
<p><em>Disadvantage</em>:</p>
<ol style="list-style-type:decimal;">
<li>Since all data is housed at one location, it might be accessible by others.</li>
</ol>
</div>
<h3>Question 2</h3>
<div><p><p>What is parallel efficiency of map-reduce means? Compare between thread, task and map-reduce.</p</p></div><div><strong>Answer:</strong><br><style>body .mathjax_wrap{width: 100%;overflow-x: scroll;margin-bottom:10px;}</style><p>Parallel efficiency of map reduce means the effectivness of utilizing computational resources and achieving speedup when executing a mapreduce job on a distributed computing system. It measures how well the system scales and utilizes available resources to perform the required computation in parallel.</p>
<p>$$Parallel Efficiency = \frac{{Actual Speedup}}{{number of processor}}*100$$</p>
<p>Here, SpeedUp represents the improvement in performance achieved by parallel execution compared to a sequential execution. A parallel efficiency of 100% indicates that parallel execution is utilizing all available resources effictively. However, in practice achieving 100% is challenging.</p>
<p>Let us assume that the data produced sfter the map phase is σ D data (postmap). Further we assume that there are P processors. Assume WD is useful work needed to be done.</p>
<p>Now agter the map operation, each mapper writes $$\frac{{σ D}}{{P}}$$</p>
<p>data to their local disk.</p>
<p>Overheads: $$\frac{{σ D}}{{P}}$$</p>
<p>Next, this data has to be read by each reduces before it can begin &#8216;reduce operationsso each reduce has to read $$\frac{{σ D}}{{P^2}}$$ i.e one path of data from particular mapper. Since, there are P different reduces, the communication time that a reducer spends getting the data it requires from different mappers as: $$\frac{{σ D}}{{P}}$$</p>
<p><img data-recalc-dims="1" loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="alignnone wp-image-36943" src="https://i0.wp.com/hamrocsit.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/WhatsApp-Image-2024-05-31-at-6.34.56-PM.jpeg?resize=474%2C130&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="474" height="130"></p>
<p>The different thread, task and map-reduce are given below:</p>
